The problem with your algorith is the part when you find a new shorter path to a node that is already in the queue.  You should not set `current` outside the call to `poll` as this breaks the algorithms scheme.  Instead you should decrease the key/priority/current-shortest-path-cost of the node.

I&#39;ve updated your code to do this.  It provides the expected result.  But like I said in a comment, when it comes to asymptotic complexity this is not the most efficient solution.  The best option is to find or write a `PriorityQueue` that supports dynamically keys efficiently.

